ga4O(){return"Photon API"},
ga58(){return"For geocoding addresses, the Photon API is used, which is licensed under the **Apache License, Version 2.0**. For more information about Photon API and its licensing, please visit: https://photon.komoot.io/."},
ga1z(){return"EFA API of MVV"},
ga56(){return"For route planning and finding transportation options, we use the **EFA API** from the Munich Transport and Tariff Association (MVV). Through this API, information about public transport and sharing services from **ShareNow** and **Call a Bike** is provided. No personal data is stored or passed on to these providers."},
ga0y(){return"Data Security"},
ga5c(){return"We implement technical and organizational measures to ensure the security of the data processed by the app. As no personal data is stored, the risk of a data protection breach is minimal."},
ga08(){return"Cookies"},
ga55(){return"This app does not use cookies or similar tracking technologies."},
ga7w(){return"Your Rights"},
ga5b(){return"Since no personal data is processed in this app, the rights of access, rectification, deletion, or restriction of processing according to Art. 15-18 GDPR are not applicable. If you still have questions regarding data protection in relation to the use of the app, you can contact us using the above contact information."},
ga_P(){return"Changes to this Privacy Policy"},
ga53(){return"We reserve the right to adjust this privacy policy to ensure it always complies with current legal requirements or to reflect changes to the app. Users will be informed of any changes in due time."},
ga6j(){return"The Project"},
ga6k(){return"This tool was developed as part of the SASIM research project, which is one of 14 projects in the first implementation phase of the Munich Cluster for the Future of Mobility in Metropolitan Regions (MCube). MCube is a future cluster funded by the BMBF, aiming to establish sustainable and transformative mobility innovations.\n\nOur goal is to make the true costs of urban transportation transparent and communicate them effectively. We aim to raise awareness about the costs of air pollutants, climate damage, accidents, traffic congestion, land use, and noise generated by our mobility. By doing so, we want to promote sustainable and fair mobility behavior."},
ga6l(){return"SASIM"},
ga6m(){return"MCube"},
ga6n(){return"sustainable and transformative mobility innovations"},
ga6o(){return"true costs of urban transportation"},
ga6p(){return u.X},
ga6q(){return"sustainable and fair mobility behavior"},
ga6s(){return"The Web App"},
ga6t(){return"The current status quo is that the costs caused by our mobility behavior are not fairly distributed. At the moment, we only pay for the private, internal costs of our mobility (e.g. fuel costs, ticket prices, or repair costs), but not the societal, external costs such as accident costs or noise costs. These are borne by society! Thus, those who cause high external costs through their mobility behavior are just as involved as those who cause low costs.\n\nThis freely available online tool evaluates individual route requests depending on the means of transportation. For now, the tool only calculates and evaluates routes within the city of Munich."},
ga6u(){return"not fairly distributed"},
ga6v(){return"not the societal, external costs"},
ga6w(){return"This freely available online tool evaluates individual route requests depending on the means of transportation."},
ga6e(){return"The Mobi-Score"},
ga6f(){return"The evaluation in this tool takes into account the costs of air pollutants, climate damage, accidents, traffic congestion, land use, and noise. For each request, these costs are then illustrated for each selected mode of transport using the MobiScore."},
ga6g(){return u.X},
ga6h(){return"The MobiScore evaluates the true costs of our individual mobility and raises awareness of \u201cinvisible\u201d costs."},
ga6i(){return"It provides an indication of how fair certain modes of transport are for any given route."},
ga6r(){return"Who else is behind Mobi-Score?"},
ga4L(){return"The calculations of personal costs are largely based on the study by K\xf6nig et al. (2021). The full cost calculator uses the following cost rates (in euros per passenger-kilometer, unless otherwise stated):"},
ga4M(){return"K\xf6nig et al. (2021)"},
gPU(){return"The calculations of external costs are based on the study by Schr\xf6der et. al (2023). The full cost calculator uses the following cost rates (in cents per passenger-kilometer):"},
gPV(){return"Schr\xf6der et al. (2023)"},
ga67(){return"Routing"},
ga68(){return"The full cost calculator uses the software OpenTripPlanner (OTP) for route planning.\nBased on the inputs (start and destination address and selected travel mode), distance, travel time and the waypoints of the route are calculated.\n\nIn order to calculate routes and travel costs by public transportation, the timetable information system DEFAS is accessed via an API."},
